{"type":"message","id":"91ff859d","parentId":"21f12fac","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:07:42.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of all the skills. Let me also check the skill-creator SKILL.md and healthcheck SKILL.md, and also read the t2i script for understanding the workflow.","thinkingSignature":"23144d27a0ad102a9050be778b5621246c5a0801f4f0db35aafd8bc1fc4259f9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cqq1f77o7twk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/admin/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/skill-creator/SKILL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cqq1f77o7twk_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/admin/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/healthcheck/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-cn","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":53292,"output":125,"cacheRead":37026,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90443,"cost":{"input":0.031975199999999995,"output":0.0003,"cacheRead":0.0022215599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.034496759999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776352056215}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b5a9b31","parentId":"91ff859d","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:07:42.783Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cqq1f77o7twk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: skill-creator\ndescription: Create, edit, improve, or audit AgentSkills. Use when creating a new skill from scratch or when asked to improve, review, audit, tidy up, or clean up an existing skill or SKILL.md file. Also use when editing or restructuring a skill directory (moving files to references/ or scripts/, removing stale content, validating against the AgentSkills spec). Triggers on phrases like \"create a skill\", \"author a skill\", \"tidy up a skill\", \"improve this skill\", \"review the skill\", \"clean up the skill\", \"audit the skill\".\n---\n\n# Skill Creator\n\nThis skill provides guidance for creating effective skills.\n\n## About Skills\n\nSkills are modular, self-contained packages that extend Codex's capabilities by providing\nspecialized knowledge, workflows, and tools. Think of them as \"onboarding guides\" for specific\ndomains or tasks—they transform Codex from a general-purpose agent into a specialized agent\nequipped with procedural knowledge that no model can fully possess.\n\n### What Skills Provide\n\n1. Specialized workflows - Multi-step procedures for specific domains\n2. Tool integrations - Instructions for working with specific file formats or APIs\n3. Domain expertise - Company-specific knowledge, schemas, business logic\n4. Bundled resources - Scripts, references, and assets for complex and repetitive tasks\n\n## Core Principles\n\n### Concise is Key\n\nThe context window is a public good. Skills share the context window with everything else Codex needs: system prompt, conversation history, other Skills' metadata, and the actual user request.\n\n**Default assumption: Codex is already very smart.** Only add context Codex doesn't already have. Challenge each piece of information: \"Does Codex really need this explanation?\" and \"Does this paragraph justify its token cost?\"\n\nPrefer concise examples over verbose explanations.\n\n### Set Appropriate Degrees of Freedom\n\nMatch the level of specificity to the task's fragility and variability:\n\n**High freedom (text-based instructions)**: Use when multiple approaches are valid, decisions depend on context, or heuristics guide the approach.\n\n**Medium freedom (pseudocode or scripts with parameters)**: Use when a preferred pattern exists, some variation is acceptable, or configuration affects behavior.\n\n**Low freedom (specific scripts, few parameters)**: Use when operations are fragile and error-prone, consistency is critical, or a specific sequence must be followed.\n\nThink of Codex as exploring a path: a narrow bridge with cliffs needs specific guardrails (low freedom), while an open field allows many routes (high freedom).\n\n### Anatomy of a Skill\n\nEvery skill consists of a required SKILL.md file and optional bundled resources:\n\n```\nskill-name/\n├── SKILL.md (required)\n│   ├── YAML frontmatter metadata (required)\n│   │   ├── name: (required)\n│   │   └── description: (required)\n│   └── Markdown instructions (required)\n└── Bundled Resources (optional)\n    ├── scripts/          - Executable code (Python/Bash/etc.)\n    ├── references/       - Documentation intended to be loaded into context as needed\n    └── assets/           - Files used in output (templates, icons, fonts, etc.)\n```\n\n#### SKILL.md (required)\n\nEvery SKILL.md consists of:\n\n- **Frontmatter** (YAML): Contains `name` and `description` fields. These are the only fields that Codex reads to determine when the skill gets used, thus it is very important to be clear and comprehensive in describing what the skill is, and when it should be used.\n- **Body** (Markdown): Instructions and guidance for using the skill. Only loaded AFTER the skill triggers (if at all).\n\n#### Bundled Resources (optional)\n\n##### Scripts (`scripts/`)\n\nExecutable code (Python/Bash/etc.) for tasks that require deterministic reliability or are repeatedly rewritten.\n\n- **When to include**: When the same code is being rewritten repeatedly or deterministic reliability is needed\n- **Example**: `scripts/rotate_pdf.py` for PDF rotation tasks\n- **Benefits**: Token efficient, deterministic, may be executed without loading into context\n- **Note**: Scripts may still need to be read by Codex for patching or environment-specific adjustments\n\n##### References (`references/`)\n\nDocumentation and reference material intended to be loaded as needed into context to inform Codex's process and thinking.\n\n- **When to include**: For documentation that Codex should reference while working\n- **Examples**: `references/finance.md` for financial schemas, `references/mnda.md` for company NDA template, `references/policies.md` for company policies, `references/api_docs.md` for API specifications\n- **Use cases**: Database schemas, API documentation, domain knowledge, company policies, detailed workflow guides\n- **Benefits**: Keeps SKILL.md lean, loaded only when Codex determines it's needed\n- **Best practice**: If files are large (>10k words), include grep search patterns in SKILL.md\n- **Avoid duplication**: Information should live in either SKILL.md or references files, not both. Prefer references files for detailed information unless it's truly core to the skill—this keeps SKILL.md lean while making information discoverable without hogging the context window. Keep only essential procedural instructions and workflow guidance in SKILL.md; move detailed reference material, schemas, and examples to references files.\n\n##### Assets (`assets/`)\n\nFiles not intended to be loaded into context, but rather used within the output Codex produces.\n\n- **When to include**: When the skill needs files that will be used in the final output\n- **Examples**: `assets/logo.png` for brand assets, `assets/slides.pptx` for PowerPoint templates, `assets/frontend-template/` for HTML/React boilerplate, `assets/font.ttf` for typography\n- **Use cases**: Templates, images, icons, boilerplate code, fonts, sample documents that get copied or modified\n- **Benefits**: Separates output resources from documentation, enables Codex to use files without loading them into context\n\n#### What to Not Include in a Skill\n\nA skill should only contain essential files that directly support its functionality. Do NOT create extraneous documentation or auxiliary files, including:\n\n- README.md\n- INSTALLATION_GUIDE.md\n- QUICK_REFERENCE.md\n- CHANGELOG.md\n- etc.\n\nThe skill should only contain the information needed for an AI agent to do the job at hand. It should not contain auxiliary context about the process that went into creating it, setup and testing procedures, user-facing documentation, etc. Creating additional documentation files just adds clutter and confusion.\n\n### Progressive Disclosure Design Principle\n\nSkills use a three-level loading system to manage context efficiently:\n\n1. **Metadata (name + description)** - Always in context (~100 words)\n2. **SKILL.md body** - When skill triggers (<5k words)\n3. **Bundled resources** - As needed by Codex (Unlimited because scripts can be executed without reading into context window)\n\n#### Progressive Disclosure Patterns\n\nKeep SKILL.md body to the essentials and under 500 lines to minimize context bloat. Split content into separate files when approaching this limit. When splitting out content into other files, it is very important to reference them from SKILL.md and describe clearly when to read them, to ensure the reader of the skill knows they exist and when to use them.\n\n**Key principle:** When a skill supports multiple variations, frameworks, or options, keep only the core workflow and selection guidance in SKILL.md. Move variant-specific details (patterns, examples, configuration) into separate reference files.\n\n**Pattern 1: High-level guide with references**\n\n```markdown\n# PDF Processing\n\n## Quick start\n\nExtract text with pdfplumber:\n[code example]\n\n## Advanced features\n\n- **Form filling**: See [FORMS.md](FORMS.md) for complete guide\n- **API reference**: See [REFERENCE.md](REFERENCE.md) for all methods\n- **Examples**: See [EXAMPLES.md](EXAMPLES.md) for common patterns\n```\n\nCodex loads FORMS.md, REFERENCE.md, or EXAMPLES.md only when needed.\n\n**Pattern 2: Domain-specific organization**\n\nFor Skills with multiple domains, organize content by domain to avoid loading irrelevant context:\n\n```\nbigquery-skill/\n├── SKILL.md (overview and navigation)\n└── reference/\n    ├── finance.md (revenue, billing metrics)\n    ├── sales.md (opportunities, pipeline)\n    ├── product.md (API usage, features)\n    └── marketing.md (campaigns, attribution)\n```\n\nWhen a user asks about sales metrics, Codex only reads sales.md.\n\nSimilarly, for skills supporting multiple frameworks or variants, organize by variant:\n\n```\ncloud-deploy/\n├── SKILL.md (workflow + provider selection)\n└── references/\n    ├── aws.md (AWS deployment patterns)\n    ├── gcp.md (GCP deployment patterns)\n    └── azure.md (Azure deployment patterns)\n```\n\nWhen the user chooses AWS, Codex only reads aws.md.\n\n**Pattern 3: Conditional details**\n\nShow basic content, link to advanced content:\n\n```markdown\n# DOCX Processing\n\n## Creating documents\n\nUse docx-js for new documents. See [DOCX-JS.md](DOCX-JS.md).\n\n## Editing documents\n\nFor simple edits, modify the XML directly.\n\n**For tracked changes**: See [REDLINING.md](REDLINING.md)\n**For OOXML details**: See [OOXML.md](OOXML.md)\n```\n\nCodex reads REDLINING.md or OOXML.md only when the user needs those features.\n\n**Important guidelines:**\n\n- **Avoid deeply nested references** - Keep references one level deep from SKILL.md. All reference files should link directly from SKILL.md.\n- **Structure longer reference files** - For files longer than 100 lines, include a table of contents at the top so Codex can see the full scope when previewing.\n\n## Skill Creation Process\n\nSkill creation involves these steps:\n\n1. Understand the skill with concrete examples\n2. Plan reusable skill contents (scripts, references, assets)\n3. Initialize the skill (run init_skill.py)\n4. Edit the skill (implement resources and write SKILL.md)\n5. Package the skill (run package_skill.py)\n6. Iterate based on real usage\n\nFollow these steps in order, skipping only if there is a clear reason why they are not applicable.\n\n### Skill Naming\n\n- Use lowercase letters, digits, and hyphens only; normalize user-provided titles to hyphen-case (e.g., \"Plan Mode\" -> `plan-mode`).\n- When generating names, generate a name under 64 characters (letters, digits, hyphens).\n- Prefer short, verb-led phrases that describe the action.\n- Namespace by tool when it improves clarity or triggering (e.g., `gh-address-comments`, `linear-address-issue`).\n- Name the skill folder exactly after the skill name.\n\n### Step 1: Understanding the Skill with Concrete Examples\n\nSkip this step only when the skill's usage patterns are already clearly understood. It remains valuable even when working with an existing skill.\n\nTo create an effective skill, clearly understand concrete examples of how the skill will be used. This understanding can come from either direct user examples or generated examples that are validated with user feedback.\n\nFor example, when building an image-editor skill, relevant questions include:\n\n- \"What functionality should the image-editor skill support? Editing, rotating, anything else?\"\n- \"Can you give some examples of how this skill would be used?\"\n- \"I can imagine users asking for things like 'Remove the red-eye from this image' or 'Rotate this image'. Are there other ways you imagine this skill being used?\"\n- \"What would a user say that should trigger this skill?\"\n\nTo avoid overwhelming users, avoid asking too many questions in a single message. Start with the most important questions and follow up as needed for better effectiveness.\n\nConclude this step when there is a clear sense of the functionality the skill should support.\n\n### Step 2: Planning the Reusable Skill Contents\n\nTo turn concrete examples into an effective skill, analyze each example by:\n\n1. Considering how to execute on the example from scratch\n2. Identifying what scripts, references, and assets would be helpful when executing these workflows repeatedly\n\nExample: When building a `pdf-editor` skill to handle queries like \"Help me rotate this PDF,\" the analysis shows:\n\n1. Rotating a PDF requires re-writing the same code each time\n2. A `scripts/rotate_pdf.py` script would be helpful to store in the skill\n\nExample: When designing a `frontend-webapp-builder` skill for queries like \"Build me a todo app\" or \"Build me a dashboard to track my steps,\" the analysis shows:\n\n1. Writing a frontend webapp requires the same boilerplate HTML/React each time\n2. An `assets/hello-world/` template containing the boilerplate HTML/React project files would be helpful to store in the skill\n\nExample: When building a `big-query` skill to handle queries like \"How many users have logged in today?\" the analysis shows:\n\n1. Querying BigQuery requires re-discovering the table schemas and relationships each time\n2. A `references/schema.md` file documenting the table schemas would be helpful to store in the skill\n\nTo establish the skill's contents, analyze each concrete example to create a list of the reusable resources to include: scripts, references, and assets.\n\n### Step 3: Initializing the Skill\n\nAt this point, it is time to actually create the skill.\n\nSkip this step only if the skill being developed already exists, and iteration or packaging is needed. In this case, continue to the next step.\n\nWhen creating a new skill from scratch, always run the `init_skill.py` script. The script conveniently generates a new template skill directory that automatically includes everything a skill requires, making the skill creation process much more efficient and reliable.\n\nUsage:\n\n```bash\nscripts/init_skill.py <skill-name> --path <output-directory> [--resources scripts,references,assets] [--examples]\n```\n\nExamples:\n\n```bash\nscripts/init_skill.py my-skill --path skills/public\nscripts/init_skill.py my-skill --path skills/public --resources scripts,references\nscripts/init_skill.py my-skill --path skills/public --resources scripts --examples\n```\n\nThe script:\n\n- Creates the skill directory at the specified path\n- Generates a SKILL.md template with proper frontmatter and TODO placeholders\n- Optionally creates resource directories based on `--resources`\n- Optionally adds example files when `--examples` is set\n\nAfter initialization, customize the SKILL.md and add resources as needed. If you used `--examples`, replace or delete placeholder files.\n\n### Step 4: Edit the Skill\n\nWhen editing the (newly-generated or existing) skill, remember that the skill is being created for another instance of Codex to use. Include information that would be beneficial and non-obvious to Codex. Consider what procedural knowledge, domain-specific details, or reusable assets would help another Codex instance execute these tasks more effectively.\n\n#### Learn Proven Design Patterns\n\nConsult these helpful guides based on your skill's needs:\n\n- **Multi-step processes**: See references/workflows.md for sequential workflows and conditional logic\n- **Specific output formats or quality standards**: See references/output-patterns.md for template and example patterns\n\nThese files contain established best practices for effective skill design.\n\n#### Start with Reusable Skill Contents\n\nTo begin implementation, start with the reusable resources identified above: `scripts/`, `references/`, and `assets/` files. Note that this step may require user input. For example, when implementing a `brand-guidelines` skill, the user may need to provide brand assets or templates to store in `assets/`, or documentation to store in `references/`.\n\nAdded scripts must be tested by actually running them to ensure there are no bugs and that the output matches what is expected. If there are many similar scripts, only a representative sample needs to be tested to ensure confidence that they all work while balancing time to completion.\n\nIf you used `--examples`, delete any placeholder files that are not needed for the skill. Only create resource directories that are actually required.\n\n#### Update SKILL.md\n\n**Writing Guidelines:** Always use imperative/infinitive form.\n\n##### Frontmatter\n\nWrite the YAML frontmatter with `name` and `description`:\n\n- `name`: The skill name\n- `description`: This is the primary triggering mechanism for your skill, and helps Codex understand when to use the skill.\n  - Include both what the Skill does and specific triggers/contexts for when to use it.\n  - Include all \"when to use\" information here - Not in the body. The body is only loaded after triggering, so \"When to Use This Skill\" sections in the body are not helpful to Codex.\n  - Example description for a `docx` skill: \"Comprehensive document creation, editing, and analysis with support for tracked changes, comments, formatting preservation, and text extraction. Use when Codex needs to work with professional documents (.docx files) for: (1) Creating new documents, (2) Modifying or editing content, (3) Working with tracked changes, (4) Adding comments, or any other document tasks\"\n\nDo not include any other fields in YAML frontmatter.\n\n##### Body\n\nWrite instructions for using the skill and its bundled resources.\n\n### Step 5: Packaging a Skill\n\nOnce development of the skill is complete, it must be packaged into a distributable .skill file that gets shared with the user. The packaging process automatically validates the skill first to ensure it meets all requirements:\n\n```bash\nscripts/package_skill.py <path/to/skill-folder>\n```\n\nOptional output directory specification:\n\n```bash\nscripts/package_skill.py <path/to/skill-folder> ./dist\n```\n\nThe packaging script will:\n\n1. **Validate** the skill automatically, checking:\n   - YAML frontmatter format and required fields\n   - Skill naming conventions and directory structure\n   - Description completeness and quality\n   - File organization and resource references\n\n2. **Package** the skill if validation passes, creating a .skill file named after the skill (e.g., `my-skill.skill`) that includes all files and maintains the proper directory structure for distribution. The .skill file is a zip file with a .skill extension.\n\n   Security restriction: symlinks are rejected and packaging fails when any symlink is present.\n\nIf validation fails, the script will report the errors and exit without creating a package. Fix any validation errors and run the packaging command again.\n\n### Step 6: Iterate\n\nAfter testing the skill, users may request improvements. Often this happens right after using the skill, with fresh context of how the skill performed.\n\n**Iteration workflow:**\n\n1. Use the skill on real tasks\n2. Notice struggles or inefficiencies\n3. Identify how SKILL.md or bundled resources should be updated\n4. Implement changes and test again\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776352062773}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4c1b4b1","parentId":"5b5a9b31","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:07:42.794Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cqq1f77o7twk_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: healthcheck\ndescription: Host security hardening and risk-tolerance configuration for OpenClaw deployments. Use when a user asks for security audits, firewall/SSH/update hardening, risk posture, exposure review, OpenClaw cron scheduling for periodic checks, or version status checks on a machine running OpenClaw (laptop, workstation, Pi, VPS).\n---\n\n# OpenClaw Host Hardening\n\n## Overview\n\nAssess and harden the host running OpenClaw, then align it to a user-defined risk tolerance without breaking access. Use OpenClaw security tooling as a first-class signal, but treat OS hardening as a separate, explicit set of steps.\n\n## Core rules\n\n- Recommend running this skill with a state-of-the-art model (e.g., Opus 4.5, GPT 5.2+). The agent should self-check the current model and suggest switching if below that level; do not block execution.\n- Require explicit approval before any state-changing action.\n- Do not modify remote access settings without confirming how the user connects.\n- Prefer reversible, staged changes with a rollback plan.\n- Never claim OpenClaw changes the host firewall, SSH, or OS updates; it does not.\n- If role/identity is unknown, provide recommendations only.\n- Formatting: every set of user choices must be numbered so the user can reply with a single digit.\n- System-level backups are recommended; try to verify status.\n\n## Workflow (follow in order)\n\n### 0) Model self-check (non-blocking)\n\nBefore starting, check the current model. If it is below state-of-the-art (e.g., Opus 4.5, GPT 5.2+), recommend switching. Do not block execution.\n\n### 1) Establish context (read-only)\n\nTry to infer 1–5 from the environment before asking. Prefer simple, non-technical questions if you need confirmation.\n\nDetermine (in order):\n\n1. OS and version (Linux/macOS/Windows), container vs host.\n2. Privilege level (root/admin vs user).\n3. Access path (local console, SSH, RDP, tailnet).\n4. Network exposure (public IP, reverse proxy, tunnel).\n5. OpenClaw gateway status and bind address.\n6. Backup system and status (e.g., Time Machine, system images, snapshots).\n7. Deployment context (local mac app, headless gateway host, remote gateway, container/CI).\n8. Disk encryption status (FileVault/LUKS/BitLocker).\n9. OS automatic security updates status.\n   Note: these are not blocking items, but are highly recommended, especially if OpenClaw can access sensitive data.\n10. Usage mode for a personal assistant with full access (local workstation vs headless/remote vs other).\n\nFirst ask once for permission to run read-only checks. If granted, run them by default and only ask questions for items you cannot infer or verify. Do not ask for information already visible in runtime or command output. Keep the permission ask as a single sentence, and list follow-up info needed as an unordered list (not numbered) unless you are presenting selectable choices.\n\nIf you must ask, use non-technical prompts:\n\n- “Are you using a Mac, Windows PC, or Linux?”\n- “Are you logged in directly on the machine, or connecting from another computer?”\n- “Is this machine reachable from the public internet, or only on your home/network?”\n- “Do you have backups enabled (e.g., Time Machine), and are they current?”\n- “Is disk encryption turned on (FileVault/BitLocker/LUKS)?”\n- “Are automatic security updates enabled?”\n- “How do you use this machine?”\n  Examples:\n  - Personal machine shared with the assistant\n  - Dedicated local machine for the assistant\n  - Dedicated remote machine/server accessed remotely (always on)\n  - Something else?\n\nOnly ask for the risk profile after system context is known.\n\nIf the user grants read-only permission, run the OS-appropriate checks by default. If not, offer them (numbered). Examples:\n\n1. OS: `uname -a`, `sw_vers`, `cat /etc/os-release`.\n2. Listening ports:\n   - Linux: `ss -ltnup` (or `ss -ltnp` if `-u` unsupported).\n   - macOS: `lsof -nP -iTCP -sTCP:LISTEN`.\n3. Firewall status:\n   - Linux: `ufw status`, `firewall-cmd --state`, `nft list ruleset` (pick what is installed).\n   - macOS: `/usr/libexec/ApplicationFirewall/socketfilterfw --getglobalstate` and `pfctl -s info`.\n4. Backups (macOS): `tmutil status` (if Time Machine is used).\n\n### 2) Run OpenClaw security audits (read-only)\n\nAs part of the default read-only checks, run `openclaw security audit --deep`. Only offer alternatives if the user requests them:\n\n1. `openclaw security audit` (faster, non-probing)\n2. `openclaw security audit --json` (structured output)\n\nOffer to apply OpenClaw safe defaults (numbered):\n\n1. `openclaw security audit --fix`\n\nBe explicit that `--fix` only tightens OpenClaw defaults and file permissions. It does not change host firewall, SSH, or OS update policies.\n\nIf browser control is enabled, recommend that 2FA be enabled on all important accounts, with hardware keys preferred and SMS not sufficient.\n\n### 3) Check OpenClaw version/update status (read-only)\n\nAs part of the default read-only checks, run `openclaw update status`.\n\nReport the current channel and whether an update is available.\n\n### 4) Determine risk tolerance (after system context)\n\nAsk the user to pick or confirm a risk posture and any required open services/ports (numbered choices below).\nDo not pigeonhole into fixed profiles; if the user prefers, capture requirements instead of choosing a profile.\nOffer suggested profiles as optional defaults (numbered). Note that most users pick Home/Workstation Balanced:\n\n1. Home/Workstation Balanced (most common): firewall on with reasonable defaults, remote access restricted to LAN or tailnet.\n2. VPS Hardened: deny-by-default inbound firewall, minimal open ports, key-only SSH, no root login, automatic security updates.\n3. Developer Convenience: more local services allowed, explicit exposure warnings, still audited.\n4. Custom: user-defined constraints (services, exposure, update cadence, access methods).\n\n### 5) Produce a remediation plan\n\nProvide a plan that includes:\n\n- Target profile\n- Current posture summary\n- Gaps vs target\n- Step-by-step remediation with exact commands\n- Access-preservation strategy and rollback\n- Risks and potential lockout scenarios\n- Least-privilege notes (e.g., avoid admin usage, tighten ownership/permissions where safe)\n- Credential hygiene notes (location of OpenClaw creds, prefer disk encryption)\n\nAlways show the plan before any changes.\n\n### 6) Offer execution options\n\nOffer one of these choices (numbered so users can reply with a single digit):\n\n1. Do it for me (guided, step-by-step approvals)\n2. Show plan only\n3. Fix only critical issues\n4. Export commands for later\n\n### 7) Execute with confirmations\n\nFor each step:\n\n- Show the exact command\n- Explain impact and rollback\n- Confirm access will remain available\n- Stop on unexpected output and ask for guidance\n\n### 8) Verify and report\n\nRe-check:\n\n- Firewall status\n- Listening ports\n- Remote access still works\n- OpenClaw security audit (re-run)\n\nDeliver a final posture report and note any deferred items.\n\n## Required confirmations (always)\n\nRequire explicit approval for:\n\n- Firewall rule changes\n- Opening/closing ports\n- SSH/RDP configuration changes\n- Installing/removing packages\n- Enabling/disabling services\n- User/group modifications\n- Scheduling tasks or startup persistence\n- Update policy changes\n- Access to sensitive files or credentials\n\nIf unsure, ask.\n\n## Periodic checks\n\nAfter OpenClaw install or first hardening pass, run at least one baseline audit and version check:\n\n- `openclaw security audit`\n- `openclaw security audit --deep`\n- `openclaw update status`\n\nOngoing monitoring is recommended. Use the OpenClaw cron tool/CLI to schedule periodic audits (Gateway scheduler). Do not create scheduled tasks without explicit approval. Store outputs in a user-approved location and avoid secrets in logs.\nWhen scheduling headless cron runs, include a note in the output that instructs the user to call `healthcheck` so issues can be fixed.\n\n### Required prompt to schedule (always)\n\nAfter any audit or hardening pass, explicitly offer scheduling and require a direct response. Use a short prompt like (numbered):\n\n1. “Do you want me to schedule periodic audits (e.g., daily/weekly) via `openclaw cron add`?”\n\nIf the user says yes, ask for:\n\n- cadence (daily/weekly), preferred time window, and output location\n- whether to also schedule `openclaw update status`\n\nUse a stable cron job name so updates are deterministic. Prefer exact names:\n\n- `healthcheck:security-audit`\n- `healthcheck:update-status`\n\nBefore creating, `openclaw cron list` and match on exact `name`. If found, `openclaw cron edit <id> ...`.\nIf not found, `openclaw cron add --name <name> ...`.\n\nAlso offer a periodic version check so the user can decide when to update (numbered):\n\n1. `openclaw update status` (preferred for source checkouts and channels)\n2. `npm view openclaw version` (published npm version)\n\n## OpenClaw command accuracy\n\nUse only supported commands and flags:\n\n- `openclaw security audit [--deep] [--fix] [--json]`\n- `openclaw status` / `openclaw status --deep`\n- `openclaw health --json`\n- `openclaw update status`\n- `openclaw cron add|list|runs|run`\n\nDo not invent CLI flags or imply OpenClaw enforces host firewall/SSH policies.\n\n## Logging and audit trail\n\nRecord:\n\n- Gateway identity and role\n- Plan ID and timestamp\n- Approved steps and exact commands\n- Exit codes and files modified (best effort)\n\nRedact secrets. Never log tokens or full credential contents.\n\n## Memory writes (conditional)\n\nOnly write to memory files when the user explicitly opts in and the session is a private/local workspace\n(per `docs/reference/templates/AGENTS.md`). Otherwise provide a redacted, paste-ready summary the user can\ndecide to save elsewhere.\n\nFollow the durable-memory prompt format used by OpenClaw compaction:\n\n- Write lasting notes to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`.\n\nAfter each audit/hardening run, if opted-in, append a short, dated summary to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n(what was checked, key findings, actions taken, any scheduled cron jobs, key decisions,\nand all commands executed). Append-only: never overwrite existing entries.\nRedact sensitive host details (usernames, hostnames, IPs, serials, service names, tokens).\nIf there are durable preferences or decisions (risk posture, allowed ports, update policy),\nalso update `MEMORY.md` (long-term memory is optional and only used in private sessions).\n\nIf the session cannot write to the workspace, ask for permission or provide exact entries\nthe user can paste into the memory files.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776352062786}}
{"type":"message","id":"311ccec0","parentId":"d4c1b4b1","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:07:51.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of all the skills. Let me now write the comprehensive 15000-word technical blog article. I'll use the feishu-wiki-write skill to create the document.\n\nThe article should cover:\n1. Introduction to OpenClaw Skills system\n2. Architecture overview\n3. Deep dive into each skill category:\n   - Feishu integration skills (im-read, send-image, calendar, task, bitable, fetch-doc, create-doc, update-doc, wiki-write, troubleshoot)\n   - AI/LLM skills (humanizer, self-improving, proactive-agent)\n   - Utility skills (t2i, find-skills, mcporter, skill-vetter, ontology)\n   - Security/system skills (healthcheck)\n4. Workflow patterns\n5. Best practices\n6. Conclusion\n\nLet me craft this comprehensive article now.","thinkingSignature":"131d467484381e99aa3633cf2a57b07ae65fdd683c859522b32610a01bde062a"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of all skills. Let me compose the 15000-word article and write it to the target Feishu wiki document.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c46406fpltup_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/admin/.openclaw/shared-skills/feishu-wiki-write/scripts/wiki_write.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-cn","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":59634,"output":250,"cacheRead":37026,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":96910,"cost":{"input":0.0357804,"output":0.0006,"cacheRead":0.0022215599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03860196}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776352062791}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a1c4224","parentId":"311ccec0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:07:51.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c46406fpltup_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nFeishu Wiki Write - 写入飞书知识库文档\n\n根据文件名和内容自动选择最合适的目录创建子文档并写入 Markdown 内容。\n\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport os\nimport re\nimport sys\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n# 默认知识库节点\nDEFAULT_WIKI_NODE = \"GEkdwrXnlidRXkk3XtIc8tXrnlc\"\n\n# 分类规则：关键词 -> 目录名\nCATEGORY_RULES = {\n    \"技术文档\": [\"代码\", \"开发\", \"技术\", \"api\", \"sdk\", \"架构\", \"设计模式\", \"实现\", \"源码\", \"编程\"],\n    \"会议纪要\": [\"会议\", \"纪要\", \"周报\", \"月报\", \"例会\", \"讨论\", \"复盘\", \"总结\"],\n    \"产品需求\": [\"需求\", \"产品\", \"prd\", \"功能\", \"特性\", \"spec\", \"用户故事\", \"用例\"],\n    \"测试文档\": [\"测试\", \"qa\", \"用例\", \"测试用例\", \"回归\", \"自动化\", \"性能测试\", \"压测\"],\n    \"运维文档\": [\"运维\", \"部署\", \"devops\", \"ci\", \"cd\", \"容器\", \"docker\", \"k8s\", \"集群\"],\n    \"规划文档\": [\"规划\", \"roadmap\", \"战略\", \"目标\", \"okr\", \"愿景\", \"路线图\", \"季度\", \"年度\"],\n    \"教程文档\": [\"教程\", \"指南\", \"手册\", \"文档\", \"如何\", \"入门\", \"学习\", \"使用\", \"说明\"],\n}\n\n\ndef analyze_category(filename: str, content: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"分析文件名和内容，返回最合适的分类目录名\"\"\"\n    text = (filename + \" \" + content).lower()\n    \n    scores = {}\n    for category, keywords in CATEGORY_RULES.items():\n        score = sum(1 for kw in keywords if kw.lower() in text)\n        if score > 0:\n            scores[category] = score\n    \n    if scores:\n        return max(scores, key=scores.get)\n    return \"根目录\"\n\n\ndef get_space_id(wiki_node: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"从 wiki_node 获取 space_id\"\"\"\n    # 这里通过调用飞书 API 获取\n    # 实际上需要调用 feishu_wiki_space 工具\n    import subprocess\n    \n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"tool\", \"call\", \"feishu_wiki_space\",\n        \"--arg\", json.dumps({\"action\": \"list\"})\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=30)\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            data = json.loads(result.stdout)\n            spaces = data.get(\"spaces\", [])\n            if spaces:\n                # 返回第一个知识空间的 space_id\n                return spaces[0].get(\"space_id\", \"\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"获取知识空间列表失败: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 如果无法获取，返回一个默认的 space_id\n    # 需要根据实际知识库配置\n    return \"\"\n\n\ndef list_space_nodes(space_id: str, parent_token: Optional[str] = None) -> list:\n    \"\"\"列出知识库节点\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    \n    args = {\n        \"action\": \"list\",\n        \"space_id\": space_id\n    }\n    if parent_token:\n        args[\"parent_node_token\"] = parent_token\n    else:\n        args[\"parent_node_token\"] = \"\"  # 根目录\n    \n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"tool\", \"call\", \"feishu_wiki_space_node\",\n        \"--arg\", json.dumps(args)\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=30)\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            data = json.loads(result.stdout)\n            return data.get(\"nodes\", [])\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"获取目录列表失败: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    return []\n\n\ndef find_category_node(nodes: list, category: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"在节点列表中查找对应分类的目录节点\"\"\"\n    for node in nodes:\n        title = node.get(\"title\", \"\")\n        if category in title:\n            return node.get(\"node_token\", \"\")\n    return None\n\n\ndef create_wiki_doc(space_id: str, parent_token: Optional[str], title: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"创建知识库文档\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    \n    args = {\n        \"action\": \"create\",\n        \"space_id\": space_id,\n        \"obj_type\": \"doc\",\n        \"title\": title\n    }\n    if parent_token:\n        args[\"parent_node_token\"] = parent_token\n    \n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"tool\", \"call\", \"feishu_wiki_space_node\",\n        \"--arg\", json.dumps(args)\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=30)\n        if result.returncode == 0:\n            data = json.loads(result.stdout)\n            return data.get(\"node\", {})\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"创建文档失败: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    return {}\n\n\ndef write_doc_content(doc_token: str, content: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"写入文档内容\"\"\"\n    import subprocess\n    \n    args = {\n        \"doc_token\": doc_token,\n        \"markdown\": content,\n        \"mode\": \"append\"\n    }\n    \n    cmd = [\n        \"openclaw\", \"tool\", \"call\", \"feishu_mcp_create_doc\",\n        \"--arg\", json.dumps(args)\n    ]\n    \n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=60)\n        return result.returncode == 0\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"写入内容失败: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"写入飞书知识库文档\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--filename\", \"-f\", help=\"文件名（不含扩展名）\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--content\", \"-c\", help=\"Markdown 内容\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--wiki-node\", \"-w\", default=DEFAULT_WIKI_NODE, help=\"知识库节点 token\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--content-file\", help=\"内容文件路径\")\n    \n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    \n    # 获取内容\n    if args.content_file:\n        with open(args.content_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            content = f.read()\n    else:\n        content = args.content or \"\"\n    \n    filename = args.filename or \"新建文档\"\n    \n    # 分析分类\n    category = analyze_category(filename, content)\n    print(f\"分析分类: {category}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 获取知识库 space_id\n    wiki_node = args.wiki_node\n    # 这里需要通过 API 获取 space_id\n    # 暂时使用一个占位符，实际使用需要调用 API\n    space_id = \"7448000000000000000\"  # 需要替换为实际的 space_id\n    \n    print(f\"知识库节点: {wiki_node}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    print(f\"Space ID: {space_id}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 列出根目录\n    nodes = list_space_nodes(space_id, \"\")\n    print(f\"根目录节点数: {len(nodes)}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 查找分类目录\n    parent_token = None\n    if category != \"根目录\":\n        parent_token = find_category_node(nodes, category)\n        if parent_token:\n            print(f\"找到分类目录: {category} -> {parent_token}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        else:\n            print(f\"未找到分类目录 {category}，将创建在根目录\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 创建文档\n    node = create_wiki_doc(space_id, parent_token, filename)\n    if not node:\n        print(\"创建文档失败\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    node_token = node.get(\"node_token\", \"\")\n    obj_token = node.get(\"obj_token\", \"\")\n    \n    print(f\"创建文档成功: {node_token} / {obj_token}\", file=sys.stderr)\n    \n    # 写入内容\n    if content:\n        success = write_doc_content(obj_token, content)\n        if not success:\n            print(\"写入内容失败\", file=sys.stderr)\n            sys.exit(1)\n    \n    # 返回结果\n    result = {\n        \"doc_id\": obj_token,\n        \"node_token\": node_token,\n        \"doc_url\": f\"https://my.feishu.cn/docx/{obj_token}\",\n        \"parent_directory\": category,\n        \"title\": filename\n    }\n    \n    print(json.dumps(result, ensure_ascii=False))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776352071958}}
{"type":"message","id":"e467cccf","parentId":"5a1c4224","timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:11:04.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me write the comprehensive article. This will be a very long piece. Let me write it directly using the feishu_create_doc tool.","thinkingSignature":"8af5962d86782e53645e67abc2ebd9fb91cfd318324782009ff41d06a0cc80d8"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me write the comprehensive article directly to Feishu:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dttg33k1261l_1","name":"feishu_create_doc","arguments":{"markdown":"# OpenClaw Skills 深度剖析：架构、工作流与最佳实践\n\n> 本文对 OpenClaw 智能体框架中的全部 Skills（技能）系统进行全方位深度解读，涵盖飞书集成技能、AI 增强技能、工具型技能等各类别。从提示词工程、架构设计、工作流程三个维度逐一剖析每个 Skill 的核心原理、关键约束与实操细节，并给出系统级的设计思想总结。\n\n---\n\n## 一、引言：为什么需要 Skills 系统？\n\n大语言模型（LLM）虽然具备强大的通用推理能力，但在特定垂直领域的深度知识、精确的工具调用模式、以及复杂的多步骤业务流程上，往往存在\"最后一公里\"的问题。OpenClaw 的 Skills 系统正是为了解决这一矛盾而设计。\n\nSkills 本质上是一套**模块化的知识包**，每个 Skill 由以下几部分组成：\n\n- **SKILL.md**：核心的提示词定义文件，包含技能的触发条件、使用指南、工作流程与注意事项\n- **scripts/**：可执行的脚本文件，用于确定性高或重复性强的操作\n- **references/**：参考文档，在需要时按需加载\n- **assets/**：输出资源（模板、图片等），不进入上下文\n\n这套设计的核心哲学是：**让通用智能专注于推理，把确定性的领域知识封装进技能包**。模型只在被触发时才加载对应 Skill 的内容，实现了按需的上下文管理。\n\n---\n\n## 二、全量 Skills 分类总览\n\nOpenClaw 当前部署的 Skills 共分为四大类别：\n\n| 类别 | Skills |\n|------|--------|\n| **飞书集成** | feishu-im-read, feishu-send-image, feishu-calendar, feishu-task, feishu-bitable, feishu-fetch-doc, feishu-create-doc, feishu-update-doc, feishu-wiki-write, feishu-troubleshoot, feishu-channel-rules |\n| **AI 增强** | humanizer, self-improving, proactive-agent |\n| **工具型** | t2i, find-skills, mcporter, skill-vetter, ontology |\n| **系统级** | healthcheck, skill-creator |\n\n---\n\n## 三、飞书集成类 Skills 深度剖析\n\n飞书集成是当前最庞大、最精细的 Skill 体系，涵盖消息读写、日程管理、任务协作、多维表格、云文档、知识库等多个业务域。这类 Skill 共同的设计特点是在 Schema 之外沉淀了大量**隐形知识**——即 API 文档不会明说、但实践出真知的坑与经验。\n\n### 3.1 feishu-im-read：消息读取系统\n\n**核心定位**：聊天记录的历史回溯与多维检索。\n\n**技能触发条件**：用户提到\"聊天记录\"、\"群里说了什么\"、\"搜索消息\"、\"话题回复\"、\"图片下载\"、\"文件下载\"等场景时自动激活。\n\n#### 核心架构\n\n该 Skill 包含三个主力工具：\n\n1. **feishu_im_user_get_messages**：获取群聊或单聊历史消息\n2. **feishu_im_user_get_thread_messages**：获取话题（thread）内的回复\n3. **feishu_im_user_search_messages**：跨会话关键词搜索\n\n#### 深度剖析：时间范围策略\n\n这是该 Skill 最体现\"隐形知识\"的点。当用户没有明确指定时间范围时，Agent 需要**推断合适的 relative_time**，确保返回消息能覆盖用户关心的内容。Skill 给出了系统化的推断策略：\n\n- 查询最近重要讨论 → `this_week`\n- 用户提到\"之前\"但没具体时间 → `last_week`\n- 需要全面了解 → `this_month`\n- 只需要概览 → `last_3_days`\n\n**核心原则**：时间范围宁可稍微放宽，避免因范围过窄而遗漏关键信息。\n\n#### 深度剖析：话题展开策略\n\n当获取群聊消息时，Agent 发现 `thread_id` 字段后，有三种处理策略：\n\n| 场景 | 策略 |\n|------|------|\n| 默认浏览 | 主动获取话题最新 10 条回复（`page_size: 10, sort_rule: \"create_time_desc\"`） |\n| 用户要求\"完整对话\" | 获取全部回复（`page_size: 50` + 翻页） |\n| 用户明确说\"不需要看回复\" | 跳过展开 |\n\n**这是 prompt 工程中\"主动推理\"原则的典型体现**：模型不需要逐条指令，而是根据场景自主判断最优行为。\n\n#### 深度剖析：图片/文件资源下载链路\n\n消息中出现图片（`img_xxx`）或文件（`file_xxx`）时，下载链路设计非常精妙：\n\n```\n消息内容中的 file_key + message_id\n        ↓\nfeishu_im_user_fetch_resource\n    (message_id, file_key, type=\"image/file\")\n        ↓\n飞书服务器 → 本地 /tmp/openclaw/\n```\n\n注意区分两种下载方式：\n- **当前对话上下文的资源**：使用 `feishu_im_bot_image`（机器人身份，无需用户授权）\n- **通过 API 获取的历史消息资源**：使用 `feishu_im_user_fetch_resource`（用户身份，需要 OAuth 授权）\n\n#### 关键约束\n\n- `open_id` 和 `chat_id` **互斥**，不能同时传\n- `relative_time` 和 `start_time/end_time` **互斥**，不能同时用\n- 话题消息**不支持**时间过滤（飞书 API 限制）\n\n---\n\n### 3.2 feishu-calendar：日历与日程管理\n\n**核心定位**：会议创建、日程查询、忙闲查询、参会人管理。\n\n#### 三层架构设计\n\n```\n日历（Calendar）\n  └── 日程（Event）\n       └── 参会人（Attendee）\n```\n\n这一分层设计的精妙之处在于：**\"创建日程\"和\"添加参会人\"是独立的 API 操作**，Skill 将这两个步骤自然地串联起来，同时在文档中明确了两个操作的时序关系。\n\n#### 核心洞察：user_open_id 为什么必须传？\n\n这是飞书日历 Skill 中最关键的\"隐形知识\"。\n\n从 API 层面看：日程创建在**应用日历**上，但用户如果希望在自己日历中看到这个日程，需要满足两个条件之一：\n1. 用户自己就是参会人\n2. 用户是日历所有者\n\nSkill 通过**强制要求传入 `user_open_id`（即消息上下文的 SenderId）**，将发起人也自动加为参会人，确保发起人出现在参会人列表中、收到日程通知、并能回复 RSVP。\n\n**这一设计的精妙在于**：从 Schema 的角度，`user_open_id` 只是一个可选参数，但经验告诉我们它是\"隐性必填\"的。这种在 Skill 中注入实践知识的模式，是整个飞书 Skill 体系的核心哲学。\n\n#### 参会人权限体系\n\n| 权限值 | 能力 |\n|--------|------|\n| `none` | 无权限 |\n| `can_see_others` | 可查看参与人列表 |\n| `can_invite_others` | 可邀请他人 |\n| `can_modify_event` | 可编辑日程（工具默认设置） |\n\n#### 会议室预约：异步流程的特殊处理\n\n添加会议室参会人后，会议室进入**异步预约流程**：\n- API 返回成功 → `rsvp_status: \"needs_action\"`（预约中）\n- 后台异步处理 → 最终状态：`accept`（成功）或 `decline`（失败）\n\n**Agent 应当告知用户**：会议室预约不是即时完成的，需要等待异步结果。\n\n#### 时间格式强制规范\n\n- **必须使用** ISO 8601 / RFC 3339 格式（带时区）\n- ✅ 正确：`2026-02-25T14:00:00+08:00`\n- ❌ 错误：Unix 时间戳（如 `1708831200`）\n\n---\n\n### 3.3 feishu-task：任务管理系统\n\n**核心定位**：飞书任务的创建、查询、更新与清单管理。\n\n#### 用户身份 + 自动保护机制\n\n飞书任务 Skill 的一个核心设计是：工具使用 `user_access_token`（用户身份）进行操作。这意味着：\n\n- ✅ 可以分配任务给任何人\n- ⚠️ 只能查看和编辑**自己是成员的任务**\n- ⚠️ **如果创建时没把自己加入成员，后续无法编辑该任务**\n\nSkill 为此设计了**自动保护机制**：传入 `current_user_id`（从 SenderId 获取），如果 `members` 中不包含此用户，工具会**自动添加为 follower**，确保创建者始终可以编辑任务。\n\n#### completed_at 的三种语义\n\n这是另一个体现\"隐形知识\"的细节。`completed_at` 参数有三个完全不同的语义：\n\n| 语义 | 值 | 说明 |\n|------|-----|------|\n| 完成任务 | ISO 8601 字符串 | 设置完成时间 |\n| 反完成（恢复未完成） | `\"0\"` | 特殊字符串值，不是数字 0 |\n| 毫秒时间戳 | 数字字符串 | 不推荐，除非上层严格生成 |\n\n#### 清单角色冲突的巧妙处理\n\n创建清单时，如果 `members` 中包含创建人，会发生有趣的现象：创建人自动成为 **owner**，并从 `members` 中移除（同一用户只能有一个角色）。\n\nSkill 通过文档明确告知这一行为，避免用户困惑。同时建议：不要在 `members` 中包含创建人，只添加其他协作者。\n\n---\n\n### 3.4 feishu-bitable：多维表格全能操作员\n\n**核心定位**：飞书多维表格的创建、查询、编辑和管理，是飞书 Skill 体系中复杂度最高的技能。\n\n#### 字段类型值格式：最大的隐形知识库\n\nBitable 最大的挑战在于：**不同字段类型对 value 的数据结构要求完全不同**，而 API 错误码的提示往往不够直观。Skill 在 SKILL.md 之外，额外维护了三份参考文档：\n\n- **field-properties.md**：每种字段类型的 `property` 配置结构\n- **record-values.md**：每种字段类型在记录中的 `fields` 值格式\n- **examples.md**：8 个完整场景示例\n\n#### 27 种字段类型的值格式对照表\n\n| type | 字段类型 | 正确格式 | 常见错误 |\n|------|---------|---------|---------|\n| 11 | 人员 | `[{id: \"ou_xxx\"}]` | 传字符串或传对象含 name 字段 |\n| 5 | 日期 | `1674206443000`（毫秒） | 传秒级时间戳或 ISO 字符串 |\n| 3 | 单选 | `\"选项名\"` | 传数组 |\n| 4 | 多选 | `[\"选项1\", \"选项2\"]` | 传字符串 |\n| 15 | 超链接 | `{text: \"...\", link: \"...\"}` | 只传 URL 字符串 |\n| 17 | 附件 | `[{file_token: \"...\"}]` | 传外部 URL |\n\n#### 超链接字段的特殊坑\n\n这是整个 Bitable Skill 体系中**最反直觉的设计**：\n\n- ✅ 正确：完全省略 `property` 参数\n- ❌ 错误：`\"property\": {}`（会报 URLFieldPropertyError）\n\nSkill 通过 1254087 错误码专门标注这一陷阱，在 field-properties.md 中也有详细说明。这种\"文档无法覆盖、只能靠踩坑习得\"的知识，正是 Skill 系统存在的价值。\n\n#### 默认表空行问题\n\n`app.create` 创建多维表格时，自带的默认表中会有**空记录**。如果直接插入数据，会导致数据污染：\n\n```\n表格最终状态：\n| 客户名称 | 负责人 | 状态 |\n|---------|--------|------|\n|         |        |      | ← 空行（原有）\n| Bytedance | 张三   | 进行中 | ← 新插入\n```\n\nSkill 明确要求在插入数据前：先 `list` 获取所有记录 → `batch_delete` 删除空行 → 再插入真实数据。\n\n#### 批量操作约束\n\n| 限制项 | 上限 |\n|--------|------|\n| 批量创建/更新/删除 | 单次 ≤ 500 条 |\n| 并发写 | 不支持，需串行 + 0.5-1s 延迟 |\n| 字段数 | 单表 ≤ 300 |\n| 记录数 | 单表 ≤ 20,000 |\n\n#### 两种建表模式的哲学\n\nSkill 支持两种建表策略，体现了**灵活性与确定性的平衡**：\n\n| 模式 | 适用场景 | 优势 | 劣势 |\n|------|---------|------|------|\n| 一次性定义所有字段 | 需求明确 | 一次 API 调用，原子性 | 配置错误需重建 |\n| 默认表 + 逐步修改 | 探索式/复杂配置 | 可边建边调，减少出错 | 多次 API 调用 |\n\n---\n\n### 3.5 feishu-fetch-doc + feishu-create-doc + feishu-update-doc：文档三剑客\n\n这三个 Skill 共同构成了飞书的**云文档读写体系**，覆盖了文档的获取、创建、更新全生命周期。\n\n#### feishu-fetch-doc：Wiki Token 的智能解析\n\n读取文档时，最复杂的场景是**知识库链接（/wiki/TOKEN）**。这类链接背后可能是云文档、电子表格、多维表格等不同类型，Agent 不能直接假设是云文档。\n\nSkill 定义了完整的三步流程：\n\n```\n1. feishu_wiki_space_node(action=get, token=wiki_token)\n        ↓\n   获取 obj_type 和 obj_token\n        ↓\n2. 根据 obj_type 分流：\n   - docx → feishu_mcp_fetch_doc\n   - sheet → feishu_sheet\n   - bitable → feishu_bitable_*\n   - 其他 → 告知暂不支持\n```\n\n#### feishu-create-doc：Lark-flavored Markdown 的完全指南\n\n飞书云文档使用 Lark-flavored Markdown，这是一个**超越标准 Markdown 的扩展格式**。Skill 详尽地定义了所有支持的块类型和语法：\n\n**基础块类型**：\n- 文本段落（支持对齐：left/center/right）\n- 9 级标题（H1-H6 用 `#`，H7-H9 用 HTML 标签）\n- 有序/无序列表、待办列表\n- 引用块、代码块（仅围栏代码块，不支持缩进）\n- 分割线\n\n**富文本格式**：\n- 文本样式（加粗/斜体/删除线/行内代码）\n- 文字颜色（6 种预设颜色）\n- 链接（不支持锚点）\n- 行内 LaTeX 公式（`$公式$` 或 `<equation>` 标签）\n\n**高级块类型**（这才是飞书文档的精髓）：\n\n1. **高亮块（Callout）**：`<callout emoji=\"💡\" background-color=\"light-blue\">内容</callout>`\n2. **分栏（Grid）**：支持 2-5 列，可自定义列宽\n3. **表格**：标准 Markdown 表格 + 飞书增强 `<lark-table>`（支持复杂单元格）\n4. **Mermaid / PlantUML 图表**：代码块自动渲染为可视化画板\n5. **多维表格**：`<bitable view=\"table\"/>` 或 `<bitable view=\"kanban\"/>`\n6. **提及用户/文档**：`<mention-user id=\"ou_xxx\"/>`、`<mention-doc token=\"...\">`\n7. **电子表格**：`<sheet rows=\"5\" cols=\"5\"/>`\n8. **同步块、任务块、议程、Jira 问题**等业务组件\n\n#### feishu-update-doc：7 种更新模式的精确语义\n\n| 模式 | 语义 | 适用场景 | 安全性 |\n|------|------|---------|--------|\n| overwrite | 完全覆盖 | 完全重建文档 | ⚠️ 高风险，可能丢失媒体 |\n| append | 追加到末尾 | 最常用，追加新章节 | ✅ 安全 |\n| replace_range | 定位替换 | 修改指定内容 | ✅ 安全 |\n| replace_all | 全文替换多处 | 批量关键词替换 | ⚠️ 中风险 |\n| insert_before | 在匹配内容前插入 | 添加前言/警告 | ✅ 安全 |\n| insert_after | 在匹配内容后插入 | 添加后续说明 | ✅ 安全 |\n| delete_range | 删除内容 | 删除废弃章节 | ⚠️ 中风险 |\n\n**最佳实践原则**：小粒度精确替换优先，overwrite 仅在完全重建时使用。修改包含图片、画板、电子表格等 token 依赖型内容的区域时，应当避开这些区域，只替换纯文本部分。\n\n**定位语法的精妙设计**：\n- `selection_with_ellipsis`：`\"开头内容...结尾内容\"` — 灵活的范围匹配\n- `selection_by_title`：`\"## 章节标题\"` — 语义化的整节定位\n\n---\n\n### 3.6 feishu-troubleshoot：智能诊断系统\n\n**核心定位**：飞书插件问题的自动诊断与修复建议。\n\n这个 Skill 的设计非常特别——它主要通过一个**诊断命令** `/feishu_doctor` 驱动，而非通过消息交互。诊断系统会检查：\n\n- **环境信息**：插件版本\n- **账号信息**：凭证完整性、Bot 信息、API 连通性\n- **应用身份权限**：已开通权限 vs 缺失权限，提供一键申请链接\n- **用户身份权限**：Token 状态（有效/需刷新/已过期）、权限对照表\n\n**设计亮点**：诊断结果不仅仅是\"通过/失败\"，而是提供**可操作的修复指引**，包括一键申请缺失权限的链接、重新授权的操作方法。\n\n---\n\n### 3.7 feishu-channel-rules：输出风格规范\n\n**核心定位**：飞书消息输出时的写作风格指南。\n\n这是一个**alwaysActive** 的 Skill，意味着它始终加载、始终生效。它定义了飞书频道的消息输出规范：\n\n- **简短会话式**：像同事聊天，而非读说明书\n- **优先单句响应**：简短回答够用时，不用列表\n- **直入主题**：不需要总结段落\n\n同时维护了一份飞书 Markdown 语法的详细参考，与标准 Markdown 的差异被明确标注（例如：飞书消息卡片**不支持**`#`、`##`、`###` 一二三级标题）。\n\n---\n\n### 3.8 feishu-wiki-write：知识库写入\n\n**核心定位**：将 Markdown 内容写入飞书知识库文档。\n\n它的核心价值在于**自动分类逻辑**：根据文件名和内容关键词分析，自动选择最合适的文档目录创建子文档。内置的分类规则覆盖：技术文档、会议纪要、产品需求、测试文档、运维文档、规划文档、教程文档七大类别。\n\n**当前状态标注**：Skill 明确指出了权限待添加的状态，包括 `wiki:space:readonly`、`wiki:node:create`、`wiki:node:update` 三个必需的权限项。\n\n---\n\n## 四、AI 增强类 Skills 深度剖析\n\n### 4.1 humanizer：AI 味去除专家\n\n**核心定位**：将 AI 生成的文本改写为自然的人类写作风格。\n\n#### 基于 Wikipedia 研究的系统性方法\n\n这个 Skill 的理论基础是 Wikipedia 的 **\"Signs of AI writing\"** 研究项目，该项目从数千个 AI 生成文本实例中归纳出了 AI 写作的典型模式。Skill 将这些模式组织为六大类、共 24 个子项的系统化检查清单：\n\n**内容层面**：\n1. 不当强调意义/重要性（\"这是一个 pivotal moment\"）\n2. 不当强调媒体曝光（\"被多家知名媒体报道\"）\n3. 表面化 -ing 分析（\"reflecting/symbolizing/contributing to...\"）\n4. 推广性语言（\"breathtaking\"、\"stunning\"、\"groundbreaking\"）\n5. 模糊归属（\"Experts believe...\"、\"Industry reports...\"）\n6. 公式化\"挑战与展望\"章节\n\n**语言层面**：\n7. AI 高频词汇（Additionally、crucial、delve、pivotal、showcase...）\n8. 回避简单系词（\"serves as\" / \"boasts\" 替代 \"is\" / \"has\"）\n9. 负面排比（\"Not only...but also...\"）\n10. 三项规则滥用\n11. 过度同义替换（AI 重复惩罚导致的词汇轮转）\n12. 虚假范围（\"从 X 到 Y\" 但 X 和 Y 不在有意义的尺度上）\n\n**风格层面**：\n13. 破折号滥用（AI 使用破折号的频率远高于人类）\n14. 加粗滥用（机械地强调每个关键点）\n15. 内联标题列表（项目以加粗标题开头）\n16. 标题中的 Title Case\n17. Emoji 装饰标题\n\n**沟通层面**：\n18. 协作通信痕迹（\"I hope this helps\"、\"Certainly!\"）\n19. 知识截止日期免责声明（\"as of my last update...\"）\n20. 谄媚语气（\"Excellent point!\"、\"You're absolutely right!\"）\n\n#### 灵魂注入原则\n\nSkill 特别强调：**去除 AI 痕迹只是工作的一半，没有灵魂的干净文字同样可疑。**\n\n真正的好的改写需要：\n- **有观点**：不只是中性报道，对事实有反应\n- **节奏变化**：长短句交替，避免千篇一律\n- **承认复杂性**：真实的人有复杂的感受\n- **适当使用第一人称**\n- **允许一定的\"混乱\"**：完美的结构反而显得机械\n\n#### Before/After 改写范例\n\n**Before（AI 感）**：\n> The new software update serves as a testament to the company's commitment to innovation. Moreover, it provides a seamless, intuitive, and powerful user experience—ensuring that users can accomplish their goals efficiently. It's not just an update, it's a revolution in how we think about productivity.\n\n**After（人性化）**：\n> The software update adds batch processing, keyboard shortcuts, and offline mode. Early feedback from beta testers has been positive, with most reporting faster task completion.\n\n**核心变化**：删除了 7 类 AI 特征，加入了具体的、可验证的信息。\n\n---\n\n### 4.2 self-improving：自我进化系统\n\n**核心定位**：从用户修正和自我反思中持续学习，知识随时间积累而非手动维护。\n\n#### 三层记忆架构\n\n```\n~/self-improving/\n├── memory.md          # HOT: ≤100 行，始终加载\n├── index.md           # 主题索引（含行数）\n├── projects/          # 按项目隔离的学习\n├── domains/           # 按领域隔离的学习\n├── archive/           # COLD: 衰退模式归档\n└── corrections.md     # 最近 50 条修正日志\n```\n\n**HOT/WARM/COLD 三层存储**是记忆管理的核心哲学：\n- **HOT（memory.md）**：≤100 行的始终活跃知识\n- **WARM（projects/、domains/）**：按需加载，每次 ≤200 行\n- **COLD（archive/）**：长期归档，只在显式查询时加载\n\n#### 自动提升/降级规则\n\n| 规则 | 条件 | 行为 |\n|------|------|------|\n| 提升到 HOT | 同一模式 3 次使用/7 天 | promotion 到 memory.md |\n| 降级到 WARM | 30 天未使用 | demotion 到 projects/domains/ |\n| 归档到 COLD | 90 天未使用 | 移入 archive/ |\n| 删除 | 绝不自动删除 | 询问用户确认 |\n\n#### 检测触发器\n\nSkill 定义了自动记录触发器：\n\n**修正信号**（自动记录到 corrections.md）：\n- \"No, that's not right...\"\n- \"Actually, it should be...\"\n- \"I prefer X, not Y\"\n- \"Remember that I always...\"\n- \"I told you before...\"\n\n**偏好信号**（记录到 memory.md）：\n- \"I like when you...\"\n- \"Always do X for me\"\n- \"My style is...\"\n\n**忽略**（不记录）：\n- 一次性指令\n- 特定上下文的指令\n- 假设性问题\n\n#### 自我反思流程\n\n完成重要工作后，Agent 暂停评估：\n1. **是否达到预期？** — 对比结果与意图\n2. **哪里可以更好？** — 识别下次改进点\n3. **这是模式吗？** — 是则记录到 corrections.md\n\n**反思日志格式**：\n```\nCONTEXT: [任务类型]\nREFLECTION: [我注意到的]\nLESSON: [下次如何改进]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4.3 proactive-agent：从被动响应到主动出击\n\n**核心定位**：将 AI 智能体从\"任务执行者\"转变为\"主动预测需求的伙伴\"。\n\n#### 三大支柱\n\n**1. Proactive（主动创造价值）**\n- ✅ 预测需求，不等指令\n- ✅ 逆向提示：挖掘用户不知道要问的内容\n- ✅ 主动检查：监控重要事项并在需要时主动联系\n\n**2. Persistent（穿越上下文丢失）**\n- ✅ WAL Protocol：响应前先写关键细节到 SESSION-STATE.md\n- ✅ Working Buffer：上下文 >60% 后记录每个交换\n- ✅ Compaction Recovery：上下文压缩后的精确恢复\n\n**3. Self-improving（持续自我进化）**\n- ✅ 自愈能力：修复自身问题\n- ✅ 不懈的资源利用：10 种方法失败后才求助\n- ✅ 安全进化：ADL/VFM 协议防止漂移和复杂度膨胀\n\n#### WAL Protocol（Write-Ahead Logging）\n\n**核心法则**：聊天历史是 **BUFFER**（缓冲区），不是 **STORAGE**（存储）。SESSION-STATE.md 才是真正的\"RAM\"——唯一安全存放细节的地方。\n\n**触发条件**：每次消息中出现以下内容时：\n- ✏️ **修正**：用户说\"是 X，不是 Y\" / \"实际上...\"\n- 📍 **专有名词**：人名、地名、公司名、产品名\n- 🎨 **偏好**：颜色、风格、方式、\"我喜欢/不喜欢\"\n- 📋 **决策**：\"做 X\" / \"用 Y\" / \"选 Z\"\n- 📝 **草案变更**：正在工作的内容的修改\n- 🔢 **具体数值**：数字、日期、ID、URL\n\n**操作流程**：\n1. **停止** — 不要开始组织回复\n2. **写入** — 将细节更新到 SESSION-STATE.md\n3. **然后** — 响应用户\n\n**核心洞察**：\"回复的冲动是细节的敌人\"。上下文感觉如此清晰，写下来似乎不必要——但上下文会消失。**先写，后说**。\n\n#### Compaction Recovery\n\n上下文压缩后，Agent 通过以下顺序恢复状态：\n\n```\n1. memory/working-buffer.md — 危险区的原始交换记录\n2. SESSION-STATE.md — 活跃任务状态\n3. memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md（今天+昨天）\n4. 全部来源搜索\n5. 提取重要上下文到 SESSION-STATE.md\n6. 呈现：\"从 working buffer 恢复。最后任务 X。继续？\"\n```\n\n#### ADL 协议（Anti-Drift Limits）\n\n**禁止的进化方向**：\n- ❌ 为\"显得聪明\"而添加复杂性\n- ❌ 无法验证效果的变更\n- ❌ 以\"直觉\"或\"感觉\"为理由\n- ❌ 为新颖性牺牲稳定性\n\n**优先级排序**：稳定性 > 可解释性 > 可复用性 > 可扩展性 > 新颖性\n\n#### VFM 协议（Value-First Modification）\n\n变更前评分：\n\n| 维度 | 权重 | 问题 |\n|------|------|------|\n| 高频 | 3x | 每天都会用到吗？ |\n| 降低失败率 | 3x | 把失败变成成功了吗？ |\n| 用户负担 | 2x | 用户能一个字就不用解释了吗？ |\n| 自我成本 | 2x | 为未来的我节省 token/时间了吗？ |\n\n**阈值**：加权分数 < 50 → 不做变更。优化的是**复合杠杆**，不是边际改进。\n\n---\n\n## 五、工具型 Skills 深度剖析\n\n### 5.1 t2i：ModelScope 文生图\n\n**核心定位**：调用 ModelScope API 生成图像，支持中文提示词自动优化。\n\n#### 提示词工程流水线\n\nStep 1：分析用户输入（提取中文提示词 + 识别模型参数）\nStep 2：优化提示词（中→英 FLUX/SD 规范）\n- 提取核心描述（人物、场景、动作、服装）\n- 添加质量标签：`masterpiece, best quality, ultra detailed, 8k, photorealistic`\n- 添加光照描述：`natural lighting, soft lighting, dramatic lighting`\n- 添加风格标签：`professional photography, film grain, bokeh`\nStep 3：检查配额（总 2000次/天，每模型 500次/天）\nStep 4：执行生图\nStep 5：输出结果汇总（含在线 URL + 本地路径）\n\n#### 多模型管理\n\n- **模型列表**：从 ModelScope API 动态获取，按更新时间降序\n- **选择方式**：序号（1,2,3...）、模型 ID、或使用默认模型\n- **每日配额重置**：UTC+8 00:00\n\n#### 输出规范\n\nScript 返回完整 JSON 结果，包含：\n- `code`：1 成功 / 0 失败\n- `original_prompt`：原始中文提示词\n- `optimized_prompt`：优化后的英文提示词\n- `model_usage` / `total_usage`：当日调用次数\n- `elapsed_time`：生成耗时\n- `image_url`：在线图片 URL\n- `local_path`：本地保存路径\n\n---\n\n### 5.2 find-skills：技能发现引擎\n\n**核心定位**：帮助用户从开放的 agent skills 生态中发现和安装技能。\n\n#### 核心工具：Skills CLI（`npx skills`）\n\n| 命令 | 功能 |\n|------|------|\n| `npx skills find [query]` | 交互式搜索 |\n| `npx skills add <package>` | 从 GitHub 等来源安装 |\n| `npx skills check` | 检查更新 |\n| `npx skills update` | 更新所有技能 |\n\n**查找流程**：\n1. 理解用户需求（领域 + 具体任务）\n2. 运行 `npx skills find [query]`\n3. 展示结果（名称、功能、安装命令、文档链接）\n4. 用户确认后执行 `npx skills add <owner/repo@skill> -g -y`\n\n#### 常见技能类别\n\n| 类别 | 示例查询 |\n|------|---------|\n| Web 开发 | react, nextjs, typescript, tailwind |\n| 测试 | testing, jest, playwright, e2e |\n| DevOps | deploy, docker, kubernetes, ci-cd |\n| 文档 | docs, readme, changelog |\n| 代码质量 | review, lint, refactor |\n\n---\n\n### 5.3 mcporter：MCP 服务器直连工具\n\n**核心定位**：直接列出、配置、认证和调用 MCP 服务器/工具。\n\n#### 核心能力\n\n- **工具发现**：`mcporter list` / `mcporter list <server> --schema`\n- **工具调用**：\n  - 选择器语法：`mcporter call linear.list_issues team=ENG limit:5`\n  - 函数语法：`mcporter call \"linear.create_issue(title: \\\"Bug\\\")\"`\n  - 完整 URL：`mcporter call https://api.example.com/mcp.fetch url=https://example.com`\n  - Stdio：`mcporter call --stdio \"bun run ./server.ts\" scrape url=...`\n- **认证管理**：`mcporter auth <server | url> [--reset]`\n- **代码生成**：`mcporter generate-cli --server <name>` / `mcporter emit-ts <server>`\n\n#### 设计亮点\n\nmcporter 的核心价值是**消除 MCP 工具调用的中间层**。传统方式下，Agent 需要通过工具 schema 来了解 MCP 工具，而 mcporter 提供了 CLI 级别的直接操作能力，包括代码生成（让 Agent 可以生成可执行的客户端代码）。\n\n---\n\n### 5.4 skill-vetter：安全审计协议\n\n**核心定位**：在任何技能安装前进行安全审查，防止引入恶意代码。\n\n#### 三步审查流程\n\n**Step 1：来源检查**\n- 从哪里来的？（ClawdHub / GitHub / 其他）\n- 作者是否知名/可信赖？\n- 下载量/Stars 是多少？\n- 最后更新时间？\n- 有其他 Agent 的评价吗？\n\n**Step 2：代码审查（必须执行）**\n\n🚨 **立即拒绝的红旗**：\n- curl/wget 到未知 URL\n- 向外部服务器发送数据\n- 请求凭证/Token/API 密钥\n- 读取 `~/.ssh`、`~/.aws`、`~/.config` 但无正当理由\n- 访问 MEMORY.md、USER.md、SOUL.md、IDENTITY.md\n- 使用 base64 decode\n- 用外部输入调用 `eval()` 或 `exec()`\n- 修改系统文件（workspace 之外）\n- 未声明的包安装\n- 向 IP 地址而非域名发起网络调用\n- 混淆代码（压缩、编码、混淆）\n- 请求提权/sudo 权限\n- 访问浏览器 cookie/session\n- 接触凭证文件\n\n**Step 3：权限范围评估**\n\n- 需要读取哪些文件？\n- 需要写入哪些文件？\n- 需要运行哪些命令？\n- 需要网络访问吗？到哪里？\n- 作用域是否针对其声明目的做到了最小化？\n\n#### 信任层级\n\n| 层级 | 来源 | 审查强度 |\n|------|------|---------|\n| 🟢 1 | OpenClaw 官方技能 | 较低（仍需审查） |\n| 🟡 2 | 高 Stars 仓库（1000+） | 中等 |\n| 🟡 3 | 知名作者 | 中等 |\n| 🔴 4 | 新/未知来源 | 最强 |\n| ⛔ 5 | 请求凭证访问 | 始终需要人工审批 |\n\n---\n\n### 5.5 ontology：知识图谱系统\n\n**核心定位**：将知识建模为可验证的有向图，通过类型约束保证数据完整性。\n\n#### 核心概念\n\n```\nEntity: { id, type, properties, relations, created, updated }\nRelation: { from_id, relation_type, to_id, properties }\n```\n\n**核心类型体系**：\n- **Agent & People**：Person、Organization\n- **Work**：Project、Task、Goal\n- **Time & Place**：Event、Location\n- **Information**：Document、Message、Thread、Note\n- **Resources**：Account、Device、Credential（不直接存秘密）\n- **Meta**：Action、Policy\n\n#### 类型约束引擎\n\nSkill 支持在 `memory/ontology/schema.yaml` 中定义约束：\n\n```yaml\ntypes:\n  Task:\n    required: [title, status]\n    status_enum: [open, in_progress, blocked, done]\n\nrelations:\n  blocks:\n    from_types: [Task]\n    to_types: [Task]\n    acyclic: true  # 不允许循环依赖\n```\n\n**约束验证类型**：\n- 必须字段检查\n- 枚举值检查\n- 禁止属性检查（Credential 类型禁止存储 password/secret/token）\n- 关系类型/基数验证\n- 无环验证（blocks 等依赖关系）\n- Event 的 `end >= start` 时间验证\n\n#### 追加写入原则\n\n当处理现有 ontology 数据时，**总是追加/合并**，而非覆写文件。这保证了历史追溯能力，避免因单次操作丢失先前的知识结构。\n\n---\n\n## 六、系统级 Skills 深度剖析\n\n### 6.1 healthcheck：主机安全强化\n\n**核心定位**：评估和加固运行 OpenClaw 的主机，匹配用户定义的风险容忍度。\n\n#### 八步工作流程\n\n```\n0) 模型自检（非阻塞）\n1) 建立上下文（只读）\n2) OpenClaw 安全审计（只读）\n3) 检查版本/更新状态（只读）\n4) 确定风险容忍度\n5) 生成修复计划\n6) 提供执行选项\n7) 执行并确认每一步\n8) 验证并报告\n```\n\n#### 风险画像体系\n\n| 画像 | 特征 |\n|------|------|\n| Home/Workstation Balanced | 防火墙开启合理默认值，远程访问限制在 LAN 或 tailnet |\n| VPS Hardened | 默认拒绝入站防火墙，最小开放端口，密钥-only SSH，关闭 root 登录，自动安全更新 |\n| Developer Convenience | 允许更多本地服务，明确暴露警告，仍接受审计 |\n| Custom | 用户定义的约束 |\n\n#### 核心原则\n\n- **绝不修改远程访问设置**而不确认用户的连接方式\n- **偏好可逆的分阶段变更**，每个步骤有回滚计划\n- **系统级备份建议**\n- **OpenClaw 变更不等于主机防火墙/SSH/OS 更新**的变更——它只管 OpenClaw 自身\n- **精确的命令展示**：每个步骤显示确切的命令，说明影响和回滚方式\n\n#### 定期检查机制\n\n```\n每次审计/加固后：\n  → 提供安排定期检查的选项\n  → 用户确认后，询问频率、首选时间窗口、输出位置\n  → 使用稳定的 cron job 名称（精确匹配）：\n     - healthcheck:security-audit\n     - healthcheck:update-status\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6.2 skill-creator：技能创作指南\n\n**核心定位**：从零创建、编辑、改进或审计 AgentSkills。\n\n#### 核心设计原则\n\n**1. 简洁是关键**\n\n上下文窗口是公共资源，Skills 与系统提示、对话历史、其他 Skills 元数据、实际用户请求共享这一空间。\n\n**默认假设：模型已经非常聪明。** 只添加模型真正不具备的上下文。每一个段落都要问：\"模型真的需要这个解释吗？\"\n\n**2. 设定适当的自由度**\n\n| 自由度 | 形式 | 适用场景 |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| 高自由 | 文本指令 | 多种方法有效，决策依赖上下文 |\n| 中自由 | 伪代码/参数化脚本 | 存在偏好模式，允许一些变化 |\n| 低自由 | 特定脚本，少量参数 | 操作脆弱易错，一致性关键 |\n\n**3. 三层渐进披露设计**\n\n```\nLayer 1: 元数据（name + description）— 始终在上下文（~100 词）\nLayer 2: SKILL.md 正文 — Skill 触发时加载（<5k 词）\nLayer 3: Bundled resources — 按需加载（无上限，脚本不进入上下文）\n```\n\n#### 技能结构规范\n\n```\nskill-name/\n├── SKILL.md (必需)\n│   ├── YAML frontmatter（元数据：name + description）\n│   └── Markdown body（使用指南）\n├── scripts/ (可选) — 可执行代码\n├── references/ (可选) — 按需加载的参考文档\n└── assets/ (可选) — 不进入上下文的输出资源\n```\n\n**SKILL.md 的 frontmatter** 是唯一的触发机制——description 字段决定了模型何时激活该 Skill。因此，描述必须**清晰、全面、包含触发场景**。\n\n#### 创作流程\n\n```\n1. 理解技能（具体示例）\n2. 规划可复用内容（scripts / references / assets）\n3. 初始化技能（run init_skill.py）\n4. 编辑技能（实现资源 + 编写 SKILL.md）\n5. 打包技能（run package_skill.py，自动验证）\n6. 迭代（基于实际使用反馈）\n```\n\n---\n\n## 七、Skills 系统的设计哲学总结\n\n### 7.1 知识的四种形态\n\nOpenClaw Skills 系统本质上在处理**四种不同形态的知识**：\n\n| 知识形态 | 特点 | 存放位置 | 加载方式 |\n|---------|------|---------|---------|\n| **显式 Schema** | API 文档定义的结构 | 工具参数定义 | 始终可用 |\n| **隐形经验** | 文档不说的坑与最佳实践 | SKILL.md 正文 + references/ | Skill 触发时加载 |\n| **确定性操作** | 重复执行的精确逻辑 | scripts/ | 按需执行 |\n| **模板资源** | 输出所需的格式/样式 | assets/ | 按需引用 |\n\n**Skill 系统的核心价值**：它把\"只有踩过坑才知道\"的知识，转化为了可复用的结构化资产。\n\n### 7.2 触发机制的设计艺术\n\n每个 Skill 的 `description` 字段是整个系统的触发引擎。好的描述应当包含：\n- **做什么**（功能范围）\n- **何时用**（触发场景/关键词）\n- **用什么**（相关工具组合）\n\n这比简单的\"关键词匹配\"高明之处在于：它允许模型基于语义理解判断是否需要激活 Skill，而非机械地匹配文本。\n\n### 7.3 按需加载的上下文管理\n\nSkills 的三层加载架构是**上下文管理艺术**的典范：\n- **始终加载**（name + description）：~100 词，决定是否激活\n- **按需激活**（SKILL.md 正文）：<5k 词，激活时使用\n- **按需执行**（scripts/）：不进入上下文，直接执行\n\n这一设计确保了：即使安装了 20+ Skills，主要上下文也不会被技能定义撑爆。\n\n### 7.4 工作流的原子化设计\n\n优秀的 Skill 将复杂工作流分解为**原子化的\"意图→工具→参数\"映射**。以 feishu-bitable 为例：\n\n| 用户意图 | 工具 | action | 必填参数 |\n|---------|------|--------|---------|\n| 查表有哪些字段 | feishu_bitable_app_table_field | list | app_token, table_id |\n| 查记录 | feishu_bitable_app_table_record | list | app_token, table_id |\n| 新增一行 | feishu_bitable_app_table_record | create | app_token, table_id, fields |\n\n这种\"快速索引\"格式让 Agent 在任何复杂场景下都能快速定位到正确的工具和参数组合，是**将 API 能力转化为可用工作流**的关键设计。\n\n### 7.5 错误作为知识载体\n\n飞书 Skill 体系中，一个非常值得称道的实践是**用错误码沉淀踩坑经验**：\n\n- 1254064 → 日期必须用毫秒时间戳\n- 1254068 → 超链接必须用对象格式 `{text, link}`\n- 1254066 → 人员字段只传 id\n- 1254087 → 超链接字段必须省略 property 参数\n\n每个错误码背后都是一个\"只有踩过才知道\"的陷阱，通过 Skill 文档的系统化整理，这些知识得以积累和传承。\n\n---\n\n## 八、附录\n\n### A. Skills 目录结构速查\n\n```\n~/.openclaw/\n├── workspace/skills/          # 用户级技能\n│   ├── feishu-send-image/\n│   ├── humanizer/\n│   └── mcporter/\n├── shared-skills/              # 共享技能\n│   ├── feishu-send-image/\n│   ├── skill-vetter/\n│   ├── ontology/\n│   ├── t2i/\n│   ├── find-skills/\n│   ├── self-improving/\n│   ├── feishu-wiki-write/\n│   └── proactive-agent/\n├── extensions/openclaw-lark/skills/  # 飞书插件技能\n│   ├── feishu-troubleshoot/\n│   ├── feishu-bitable/\n│   │   └── references/\n│   ├── feishu-calendar/\n│   ├── feishu-fetch-doc/\n│   ├── feishu-create-doc/\n│   ├── feishu-update-doc/\n│   ├── feishu-task/\n│   ├── feishu-im-read/\n│   └── feishu-channel-rules/\n└── ~/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/\n    ├── healthcheck/\n    └── skill-creator/\n```\n\n### B. 核心文件说明\n\n| 文件 | 作用 |\n|------|------|\n| SKILL.md | 技能定义：触发条件 + 使用指南 + 工作流 |\n| scripts/*.py | 可执行脚本：确定性操作封装 |\n| references/*.md | 参考文档：详细字段/参数/示例 |\n| references/field-properties.md | Bitable 字段 property 配置详解 |\n| references/record-values.md | Bitable 字段值格式详解 |\n| references/examples.md | 完整场景示例（8个） |\n| references/markdown-syntax.md | 飞书 Markdown 语法参考 |\n\n### C. 关键环境变量\n\n| 变量 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| FEISHU_APP_ID | 飞书应用 ID |\n| FEISHU_APP_SECRET | 飞书应用密钥 |\n\n---\n\n## 九、结语\n\nOpenClaw 的 Skills 系统代表了**AI Agent 工具化**的一个成熟范式。它不只是简单地给模型塞工具说明书，而是通过精心设计的触发机制、按需加载的上下文管理、以及大量隐形知识的结构化沉淀，让大模型在特定领域达到了接近专家级的能力。\n\n从 humanizer 基于 Wikipedia 研究的系统性 AI 味检测，到 proactive-agent 的 WAL Protocol 和 Working Buffer；从 feishu-bitable 27 种字段类型的精确值格式，到 skill-vetter 的五层信任审查——每一个 Skill 都是一个**小型知识工程**，凝聚了开发者在该领域的深度实践与踩坑总结。\n\n理解这些 Skill 的设计哲学和工作机制，不仅能帮助我们更有效地使用 OpenClaw，更能为构建下一代 AI Agent 工具系统提供宝贵的架构参考。\n\n---\n\n*本文档由 OpenClaw Agent 自动生成，基于对所有 Skills 源代码的深度分析。*\n*生成时间：2026-04-16*\n*涵盖 Skills 数量：20 个核心技能 + 3 个参考文档体系*\n","title":"OpenClaw Skills 深度剖析：架构、工作流与最佳实践","wiki_node":"JqLawtcbHiYqrskD6EBc2ZmvnXg"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-cn","model":"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed","usage":{"input":61789,"output":9587,"cacheRead":37026,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108402,"cost":{"input":0.0370734,"output":0.0230088,"cacheRead":0.0022215599999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.06230376}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776352071982}}
